name: Quadriceps
description: The large muscle group on the front of the thigh.

name: Hamstrings
description: The muscle group on the back of the thigh.

name: Glutes
description: The muscles of the buttocks.

name: Lower Back
description: The muscles in the lower region of the back.

name: Lats
description: The large, flat muscles on the sides of the back.

name: Forearms
description: The muscles in the lower part of the arms, between the elbow and wrist.

name: Pectorals
description: The muscles of the chest.

name: Triceps
description: The muscle on the back of the upper arm.

name: Anterior Deltoids
description: The front part of the shoulder muscles.

name: Deltoids
description: The muscles forming the rounded contour of the shoulder.

name: Upper Chest
description: The upper portion of the pectoral muscles.

name: Biceps
description: The muscle on the front of the upper arm.

name: Abdominals
description: The muscles of the abdomen.

name: Obliques
description: The muscles on the sides of the abdomen.

name: Cardiovascular
description: Relating to the heart and blood vessels.

name: Lateral Deltoids
description: The side part of the shoulder muscles.

name: Calves
description: The muscles at the back of the lower leg.

name: Traps
description: The large muscles extending over the back of the neck and shoulders.

name: Rotator Cuff
description: A group of muscles and tendons surrounding the shoulder joint.

name: Adductors
description: Inner thigh muscles responsible for moving the legs inward.

name: Erector Spinae
description: Muscles along the spine that help with extension and rotation of the back.

name: Rhomboids
description: Muscles in the upper back between the shoulder blades.

name: Core (General)
description: Encompasses various muscles of the torso that stabilize the spine and pelvis.

name: Gastrocnemius
description: The largest muscle of the calf.

name: Soleus
description: A muscle in the calf, lying underneath the gastrocnemius.

name: Deltoid (Posterior)
description: The rear part of the shoulder muscles.

name: Serratus Anterior
description: Muscles that originate on the surface of the 1st to 8th ribs and insert along the entire medial border of the scapula.
